@node infinity
@section @code{infinity}, @code{infinityf}--representation of infinity
@findex infinity
@findex infinityf
@strong{Synopsis}
@example
#include <math.h>
double infinity(void);
float infinityf(void);

@end example
@strong{Description}@*
@code{infinity} and @code{infinityf} return the special number IEEE
infinity in double- and single-precision arithmetic
respectively.

@*
@strong{Portability}@*
@code{infinity} and @code{infinityf} are neither standard C nor POSIX.  C and
POSIX require macros HUGE_VAL and HUGE_VALF to be defined in math.h, which
Newlib defines to be infinities corresponding to these archaic infinity()
and infinityf() functions in floating-point implementations which do have
infinities.

